// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Padding buffer (the padded message). Backed by module-level `var int` byte
// slots because there are no arrays. 128 bytes is the max for SHA-256 (one
// block); inputs longer than 55 bytes need two+ blocks and are processed one
// 64-byte block at a time via blk_get/blk_set over a rolling 64-byte window.
// To keep the global count manageable we store the padded message length and
// fetch bytes directly from the original input string for the data region,
// reusing a 64-byte block buffer only for the schedule-load step.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

